{"title": "Unsanitized user input in OS command", "summary": "  Applications should not execute OS commands that are formed from user input. This rule checks for external commands containing user-supplied data. ", "description": "\n\nApplications should not execute OS commands that are formed from user input.\nThis rule checks for external commands containing user-supplied data.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using user input when executing commands:\n\n```ruby\nsystem(params[:command])\n```\n\n\u2705 Use user input indirectly when executing commands:\n\n```ruby\ncommand =\n  case params[:action]\n  when \"option1\"\n    \"command1\"\n  when \"option2\"\n    \"command2\"\n  end\n\nsystem(command)\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-78"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_lang_exec_using_user_input", "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Ruby_on_Rails_Cheat_Sheet.html#command-injection", "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/OS_Command_Injection_Defense_Cheat_Sheet.html"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}